35:03.060 --> 35:05.062
<i>In hope that someone listens ♪</i>

35:05.062 --> 35:07.564
<i>♪ Pray the Lord hears me,
innocent people going missing</i> ♪

35:07.648 --> 35:09.358
<i>On the journey to the riches ♪</i>

35:09.358 --> 35:10.859
<i>♪ While we're standing,
taking pictures...</i>

35:10.943 --> 35:12.736
You should eat.

35:12.820 --> 35:14.488
You look like hell.

35:15.739 --> 35:19.243
That's 'cause I saw you
gouge a man's eyes out.

35:19.243 --> 35:20.619
He started it.

35:21.620 --> 35:24.039
<i>♪ Finding you a new replacement,
nothing's wrong with me...</i>

35:24.039 --> 35:26.834
They might try to kill me
as soon as I'm bailed out.

35:27.876 --> 35:29.753
You important
to their operation?

35:29.837 --> 35:33.090
<i>Let me do my thing ♪</i>

35:33.090 --> 35:35.092
<i>♪ Yes, I felt my pain...</i>

35:35.092 --> 35:37.594
Real important.

35:37.678 --> 35:39.179
Then you're probably okay.

35:39.263 --> 35:42.182
But bodies are falling.
Means someone's getting nervous.

35:43.392 --> 35:45.644
When that happens,
things can change fast.

35:47.521 --> 35:50.440
I'm more curious why whoever
you work for wants me dead.

35:50.524 --> 35:52.359
- What do you mean?
- That guard from last night,

35:52.359 --> 35:54.319
Spivey,

35:54.403 --> 35:56.363
he set us up in gen pop.

35:56.363 --> 35:58.740
He'd play it off like it was
some kind of innocent mistake,

35:58.824 --> 36:00.617
but it was intentional.

36:00.701 --> 36:03.537
Guys in the shower I.D.'d me
as a person to take out.

36:04.621 --> 36:06.623
Once I'm out of here, I'm gone,

36:07.791 --> 36:09.710
Something bad's
going down in Margrave,

36:09.710 --> 36:11.795
and I don't need
to be a part of it.

36:22.264 --> 36:24.182
My wife should be here soon.

36:24.266 --> 36:25.893
I don't give a shit.

36:37.321 --> 36:40.782
Figured a guy with no money,
I.D. or car could use a lift.

36:52.544 --> 36:54.713
- That's me.
- Greyhound confirmed

36:54.713 --> 36:56.465
that's their Tampa station
two nights ago.

36:56.465 --> 36:58.717
No way you could've been in
Margrave in time to kill anyone.

36:58.717 --> 37:01.470
Common carriers are
notoriously difficult.

37:01.470 --> 37:04.348
N-Nothing without a warrant.
How'd you get them to cooperate?

37:04.348 --> 37:05.599
Lied.

37:05.599 --> 37:07.643
Said that we suspected
one of their employees

37:07.643 --> 37:09.561
of using their buses
to transport coke.

37:09.645 --> 37:11.146
If they didn't cooperate,
promised to pull

37:11.146 --> 37:12.648
a civil forfeiture
on everything with wheels

37:12.648 --> 37:14.358
until our investigation
was over.

37:14.358 --> 37:16.860
Got that video within the hour.

37:16.944 --> 37:18.111
So you cleared me,

37:18.195 --> 37:19.780
but how does the guy
who confessed walk away?

37:19.780 --> 37:21.990
Well, everybody
knows that Hubble's lying,

37:22.074 --> 37:24.493
so we're holding off on charges,

37:24.493 --> 37:27.537
hoping that a nervous guy like
him just does something dumb

37:27.621 --> 37:29.122
that leads us to the truth

37:29.206 --> 37:33.085
or just cracks and spills
what really went down.

37:33.085 --> 37:34.878
Smart approach, Officer Roscoe.

37:36.296 --> 37:38.382
Roscoe's actually my first name.

37:40.133 --> 37:42.052
Never met a woman
named Roscoe before.

37:42.052 --> 37:43.136
Yeah, you did.

37:43.220 --> 37:45.472
A day ago.

37:46.515 --> 37:48.266
So what's your last name?

37:48.350 --> 37:49.893
Conklin.

37:51.979 --> 37:53.814
Caught a love tap inside?

37:53.814 --> 37:56.108
I got set up.

37:56.108 --> 37:58.652
- By who?
- Some guard.

37:58.652 --> 38:00.320
Just the errand boy.

38:00.404 --> 38:02.280
But whoever he took orders
from wanted me gone,

38:02.364 --> 38:04.449
and they're gonna get
what they want.

38:04.533 --> 38:06.702
I'm on the next bus out of here.

38:06.702 --> 38:08.620
That's a shame.

38:09.871 --> 38:13.166
I feel bad about the Margrave
welcome wagon running you over.

38:15.293 --> 38:17.129
I was gonna apologize
with an early dinner,

38:17.129 --> 38:18.380
but if you're not
sticking around...

38:18.380 --> 38:19.673
Okay.

38:21.341 --> 38:22.551
Great.

38:24.386 --> 38:27.305
But I'm gonna need
some new clothes first.

38:27.389 --> 38:29.182
Lockup's made me a bit gamey.

38:29.266 --> 38:31.184
Oh, we got
a Merl's Men's Shop in town.

38:32.310 --> 38:34.354
I don't need anything
that fancy.

38:34.438 --> 38:35.856
Just T-shirt and jeans.

38:38.191 --> 38:39.818
I travel light.

38:43.405 --> 38:45.824
You sure you don't
want to get new threads?

38:45.824 --> 38:47.743
They'll be new to me.

38:50.203 --> 38:51.538
I don't get it.

38:51.538 --> 38:53.832
Don't you want
a home base or something?

38:53.832 --> 38:55.751
Had a home base my whole life.

38:55.751 --> 38:58.295
Grew up in the military,
worked in the military.

38:58.295 --> 39:00.213
Always told where to go,
when to be there.

39:00.297 --> 39:03.300
Now I see my country
on my own terms.

39:03.300 --> 39:04.885
What about money?

39:04.885 --> 39:07.179
Pension's wired to
a Western Union each month.

39:08.513 --> 39:10.307
Don't you miss your family?

39:10.307 --> 39:12.517
I guess so. They're all dead.

39:12.601 --> 39:14.728
Except for my brother Joe.

39:14.728 --> 39:16.813
- He's a good guy.
- Where's he?

39:18.231 --> 39:19.733
No idea.

39:21.735 --> 39:23.653
So what really
brought you to Margrave?

39:23.737 --> 39:25.363
Can't be some blues singer.

39:25.447 --> 39:27.949
I don't lie to people
who get me out of jail.

39:28.033 --> 39:30.243
I'm here because of Blind Blake,

39:30.327 --> 39:33.080
but actually
it's on account of Chauncey.

39:33.080 --> 39:34.581
Who's Chauncey?

39:35.957 --> 39:38.794
A couple days ago, I go to
Chauncey's Bar & Grill in Tampa.

39:38.794 --> 39:41.922
Guy there was playing "Police
Dog Blues" by Blind Blake.

39:41.922 --> 39:43.381
I remembered
a conversation I had

39:43.465 --> 39:45.592
with my brother Joe
a while back.

39:45.592 --> 39:47.469
Read some article about Blake,
said he played his last show

39:47.469 --> 39:49.554
in Margrave,
and that's where he died.

39:51.056 --> 39:52.724
So I got on a bus.

39:55.143 --> 39:57.771
So you just go wherever
you want, whenever you want?

39:57.771 --> 40:00.315
Everyone's always jealous.

40:00.315 --> 40:02.400
Well, yeah, that's, um...

40:03.985 --> 40:05.695
...an interesting
approach to life.

40:05.779 --> 40:07.072
Works for me.

40:23.338 --> 40:25.090
So I'll check out
the town for a while

40:25.090 --> 40:27.008
- and see you in a bit.
- Sounds good.

40:27.092 --> 40:30.220
Now, don't go getting yourself
arrested for murder again.

40:33.849 --> 40:38.895
<i>♪ If you see my baby,
Lordy, stand around</i> ♪

40:38.979 --> 40:42.107
<i>♪ You know we somewhere,
baby, Lord, mama</i> ♪

40:42.107 --> 40:45.402
<i>♪ Shake 'em on down,
Lordy, must I low</i> ♪

41:06.923 --> 41:11.052
<i>♪ If you come to my house,
you don't find me around</i> ♪

41:11.136 --> 41:14.389
<i>♪ You know we somewhere,
baby, Lord, mama</i> ♪

41:14.389 --> 41:15.807
<i>Shake 'em on down ♪</i>

41:15.891 --> 41:17.893
<i>♪ Lordy, must I low...</i>

41:30.572 --> 41:32.824
If you want a trim,

41:32.908 --> 41:34.784
you got to wait.

41:34.868 --> 41:37.537
It's Mosley's meal time.

41:37.621 --> 41:39.706
I was thinking a shave,
Mr. Mosley.

41:39.706 --> 41:43.919
Blind alley cat
can shave and eat.

41:44.961 --> 41:48.590
Heard Mississippi Fred McDowell
coming from your shop.

41:48.590 --> 41:50.675
Thought a blues fan
might be able to tell me

41:50.759 --> 41:53.136
a bit about Blind Blake's
time in Margrave.

41:54.471 --> 41:56.181
Huh.

41:56.181 --> 42:00.936
Surprised a white man
your age knows Fred McDowell.

42:03.021 --> 42:06.441
More surprised
you know Blind Blake,

42:06.441 --> 42:07.943
Mr. Reacher.

42:09.861 --> 42:11.738
Small town.

42:11.738 --> 42:14.491
When a giant stranger
gets arrested for murder,

42:14.491 --> 42:17.494
word gets around.

42:17.494 --> 42:22.624
Course, Ms. Roscoe cleared you,
so I ain't scared of you none.

42:22.624 --> 42:25.252
My age, I ain't scared
of nothing much.

42:25.252 --> 42:27.003
Yeah, me neither.

42:27.087 --> 42:29.005
And everyone
just calls me Reacher.

42:29.089 --> 42:31.174
Even my mother did.

42:31.258 --> 42:33.677
Well, back you go.

42:38.890 --> 42:42.185
You know, my sister sang
with Blake a few times

42:42.269 --> 42:44.187
back in the day.

42:44.271 --> 42:47.148
He'd come through town
each year,

42:47.232 --> 42:51.319
play the church or some barn
in the sticks.

42:51.403 --> 42:53.530
- I heard he died here.
- That's the rumor.

42:53.530 --> 42:56.241
People would come from
all over town to hear it,

42:56.241 --> 42:58.535
even white folks.

42:58.535 --> 43:00.453
One hell
of a town it is.

43:00.537 --> 43:01.871
Freshly painted gazebo.

43:01.955 --> 43:03.832
Manicured flower beds.

43:04.958 --> 43:06.418
Statue recently polished.

43:06.418 --> 43:08.253
Got to think it's more
than civic pride.

43:08.253 --> 43:11.464
That it is.

43:11.548 --> 43:14.467
The Kliner Foundation
takes care of Margrave.

43:14.551 --> 43:17.971
Ever since Mr. Kliner came
to town about five years back

43:17.971 --> 43:20.932
from St. Louis to set up
his company right here.

43:21.016 --> 43:22.350
What kind of company is that?

43:22.434 --> 43:25.562
You name it,
Kliner do it.

43:25.562 --> 43:30.900
Real estate, trucking,
chemicals, machine parts.

43:30.984 --> 43:34.195
That statue out there?
Casper Teale?

43:34.279 --> 43:36.281
His grandson's our mayor.

43:36.281 --> 43:40.535
He gave Kliner a sweetheart
land deal for his factory.

43:40.535 --> 43:43.747
And in return, Kliner pours
money into the town.

43:43.747 --> 43:45.498
Win-win.

43:45.582 --> 43:48.335
That there
is Kliner Jr.

43:48.335 --> 43:50.879
and his bughouse cousin Dawson.

43:50.879 --> 43:53.882
Everyone calls Junior KJ.

43:53.882 --> 43:56.384
I call him trouble.

43:58.094 --> 43:59.929
Keep my seat warm, would you?

44:08.563 --> 44:11.733
You looking for a dance partner?

44:11.733 --> 44:13.360
'Cause the last person
who eyeballed me like that

44:13.360 --> 44:14.569
was a woman down in Panama

44:14.569 --> 44:15.862
when I was stationed
at Fort Sherman,

44:15.862 --> 44:18.990
and she wanted to dance
the tamborito with me.

44:19.074 --> 44:21.201
Do you want to dance
the tamborito with me?

44:21.201 --> 44:24.037
- Hell, I'll dance.
- Not talking to you, peewee.

44:24.037 --> 44:26.289
I was talking to the guy
in pricier boots,

44:26.373 --> 44:27.665
better haircut
and expensive truck

44:27.749 --> 44:29.292
he lets you sit shotgun in.

44:31.169 --> 44:32.879
So...

44:34.172 --> 44:35.799
...you want me to lead or...?

44:37.133 --> 44:38.760
I'm not much of a dancer.

44:39.761 --> 44:41.721
More of an academic
and a reader.

44:42.764 --> 44:46.017
Fact, I was reading something
interesting just this morning

44:46.101 --> 44:49.479
about some charges brought
against a Major Jack Reacher

44:49.479 --> 44:51.689
in a small village
outside of Baghdad.

44:52.732 --> 44:54.526
Charges of
a very serious nature,

44:54.526 --> 44:56.903
but charges
that somehow disappeared,

44:56.903 --> 45:00.365
like grains of sand
in an unforgiving desert.

45:00.365 --> 45:03.535
Somehow, the desert ended up
forgiving you, didn't it?

45:04.536 --> 45:06.538
We don't forgive as easily
in Margrave.

45:08.081 --> 45:09.958
Watch your back, Mr. Reacher.

45:44.701 --> 45:46.369
Hey.

45:46.453 --> 45:48.455
Sorry, dinner's
not gonna happen.

45:48.455 --> 45:50.582
- What's going on?
- Another body was found.

45:50.582 --> 45:52.167
In the brush, 40 yards
from the first one.

45:52.167 --> 45:53.626
Same caliber bullet.

45:53.710 --> 45:55.420
Got to go to the morgue.

45:55.420 --> 45:56.796
Can't say I'm not disappointed.

45:56.880 --> 45:58.298
I was looking forward
to spending time with you

45:58.298 --> 45:59.716
before leaving.

45:59.716 --> 46:01.759
Well, I don't know if you're
going anywhere just yet.

46:01.843 --> 46:03.011
Reacher!

46:03.011 --> 46:05.680
Did Hubble talk
when you two were locked up?

46:05.680 --> 46:07.474
- No.
- Baloney.

46:07.474 --> 46:08.933
Easy, Finlay.
Watch your language.

46:09.017 --> 46:10.226
You think this is funny?

46:10.310 --> 46:12.812
I got a town of 1,700 people
and two homicides.

46:12.896 --> 46:15.565
He didn't talk to me
the whole time we were in there.

46:15.565 --> 46:18.234
- I don't believe you.
- I don't care.

46:18.318 --> 46:20.653
- Dinner would've been nice.
- You're not going anywhere.

46:20.737 --> 46:22.655
My alibi cleared.

46:22.739 --> 46:24.657
Just 'cause we know you weren't
here when these bodies dropped

46:24.741 --> 46:26.868
doesn't mean you might not
have something to do with them.

46:26.868 --> 46:28.328
So I'm wondering if maybe it was

46:28.328 --> 46:31.331
some other six-foot-five gorilla
on that grainy Greyhound tape.

46:31.331 --> 46:33.541
Maybe I need to bring in
a forensic expert

46:33.625 --> 46:35.001
to confirm it was you.

46:35.001 --> 46:38.004
And maybe you need to cool
your heels back in Warburton

46:38.004 --> 46:40.673
while we get that done over
the next two or three weeks.

46:40.757 --> 46:44.302
Or you get in the car,
we go to the morgue.

46:44.302 --> 46:46.387
Perhaps the medical examiner
will say something

46:46.471 --> 46:47.931
that jars your memory
about Hubble

46:47.931 --> 46:49.474
and you can share it with me.

46:49.474 --> 46:51.518
First you make it clear
I'm not a cop anymore.

46:51.518 --> 46:52.894
Now you want my help?

46:52.894 --> 46:54.646
I want you to do what I say.

46:54.646 --> 46:55.772
Now.

47:05.240 --> 47:07.742
Sometimes you're dead
and you don't even know it.

47:07.742 --> 47:10.078
This second guy, he was shot
in the back of the head

47:10.078 --> 47:12.622
while running away,
but his legs kept pumping

47:12.622 --> 47:14.457
for a few more feet
before his brain told him,

47:14.541 --> 47:16.960
"Hey, buddy, you're dead,"
so he fell over into the weeds.

47:16.960 --> 47:20.171
At least that's what the blood
spatters at the scene said.

47:20.255 --> 47:22.715
He was shot from far enough away
and it was so dark

47:22.799 --> 47:25.552
he couldn't be found, so
the killer just left him there.

47:25.552 --> 47:26.553
No I.D. on him.

47:26.553 --> 47:28.096
Killers.

47:28.096 --> 47:30.890
In an investigation,
details matter.

47:30.974 --> 47:33.309
Most likely more than one doer.

47:33.393 --> 47:34.978
Well, these are
my first murders,

47:34.978 --> 47:37.230
so please tell me you know
who did this.

47:38.940 --> 47:40.066
Mm-mm.

47:40.066 --> 47:42.068
What about
our first John Doe?

47:42.068 --> 47:44.237
- Any luck?
- Nope.

47:44.237 --> 47:46.531
He's been harder to crack
than a steel walnut.

47:46.531 --> 47:48.032
Dental work was inconsistent.

47:48.116 --> 47:50.326
Some of it was done in the U.S.,
and the rest was foreign.

47:50.410 --> 47:53.037
And his fingertips
were compromised by

47:53.121 --> 47:54.998
a dermatitis reaction.

47:54.998 --> 47:57.041
So swollen,
prints wouldn't come out clean

47:57.125 --> 47:58.710
until I drained
some of the fluid.

47:58.710 --> 48:00.420
We're waiting for the results.

48:00.420 --> 48:01.588
Whoa. No, do not...

48:01.588 --> 48:05.300
Um, is he new
on the force or...?

48:05.300 --> 48:06.884
No.

48:06.968 --> 48:08.761
Well, kind of.

48:08.845 --> 48:11.347
First victim
was allergic to latex.

48:11.431 --> 48:14.017
Killers must've worn some kind
of polyvinyl protective suit

48:14.017 --> 48:15.852
to keep blood DNA
off themselves.

48:15.852 --> 48:18.146
The victim grabbed it in the
struggle, causing his fingertips

48:18.146 --> 48:20.231
to swell in
a histaminic reaction.

48:21.399 --> 48:23.276
His dental work's off
'cause he had his teeth fixed

48:23.276 --> 48:25.361
wherever he was living
at the time.

48:25.445 --> 48:28.489
Broke his right arm when he was
eight, had it set in Berlin.

48:28.573 --> 48:31.534
Had his tonsils taken out
at ten in Seoul.

48:56.643 --> 48:57.852
We were wrestling.

49:00.313 --> 49:02.315
I pinned him against the stove.

49:04.025 --> 49:06.694
Didn't know my mother
had just turned it off.

49:11.991 --> 49:14.077
That's how my brother
got this scar.

49:22.085 --> 49:24.337
You tell me right now
what's going on.

49:24.337 --> 49:26.798
What was your brother
doing in Margrave?

49:26.798 --> 49:28.675
- I don't know.
- So it's just a coincidence

49:28.675 --> 49:31.135
you and he are passing through
the exact same Podunk town

49:31.219 --> 49:32.720
at the exact same
moment in time?

49:32.804 --> 49:34.847
- I don't know.
- When's the last time you saw Joe?

49:34.931 --> 49:36.349
A minute ago in the morgue.

49:36.349 --> 49:39.185
- You being smart with me?
- I'm being straight with you.

49:39.185 --> 49:41.104
Hell, no wonder Sharon left you.

49:42.146 --> 49:44.649
You keep my wife's name
out of your mouth.

49:44.649 --> 49:46.526
No. Enough.

49:46.526 --> 49:47.819
Reacher, you crossed a line.

49:47.819 --> 49:49.570
Finlay, let it rest.

49:49.654 --> 49:51.572
This man just lost his brother.

49:51.656 --> 49:53.700
One question,
and I want the truth.

49:53.700 --> 49:55.785
What are you doing
here in Margrave?

49:58.287 --> 49:59.664
Blind Blake!

49:59.664 --> 50:01.416
You're messing with
the wrong man.

50:01.416 --> 50:03.167
I'll tell you that right now.

50:03.251 --> 50:04.919
I swear, I'm gonna find
any reason I can

50:04.919 --> 50:06.045
to lock you up again.

50:06.129 --> 50:07.547
Oh, you won't even
get the cuffs on me.

50:07.547 --> 50:10.466
Okay, this isn't gonna happen.
Reacher, sit in the back.

50:10.550 --> 50:12.468
Hey. I know you're not
the kind of guy to beat up

50:12.552 --> 50:14.178
on somebody half your size
without good reason.

50:14.262 --> 50:15.888
- He's giving me a reason.
- Yeah?

50:15.972 --> 50:17.598
Well, I know people.

50:17.682 --> 50:19.684
And you've got kind eyes.

50:21.519 --> 50:23.062
Do what I say, Reacher.

50:23.146 --> 50:24.313
Please.

50:38.870 --> 50:40.872
You okay, Reacher?

50:42.707 --> 50:45.001
Just thinking maybe my brother
told me about Blind Blake

50:45.001 --> 50:46.169
for a reason.

50:46.169 --> 50:49.130
Thinking about him
lying in that morgue.

50:49.130 --> 50:52.133
Thinking I'm supposed
to do something about it.

50:53.176 --> 50:54.510
Like what?

50:56.429 --> 50:58.681
I guess I'll find
everybody responsible.

50:59.807 --> 51:01.809
And kill every last one of them.

